Feature: launching a BC on the fabro orchestrator path wires fabro's Anthropic provider to the in-container anthropic-oauth-shim credential bridge, with the native fabro vault holding only placeholders

  SLICE 3 of the fabro launch path (epic lead-kqgp, under lead-6k1r; S3 work_id
  lead-vwib, target shopsystem-bc-launcher, assign_scenarios). S1 (scenario 73,
  @scenario_hash:a3512aedb8763150) baked the fabro SUBSTRATE — the fabro binary
  v0.254.0 and the anthropic-oauth-shim — into bc-base:latest. S2 (scenario 75,
  @scenario_hash:2dfefe2ba81e418d) made the launcher ship+place a self-contained,
  valid fabro def whose native vault carries only "__PLACEHOLDER__". Substrate
  plus def orchestrates locally but cannot reach a real LLM: fabro's built-in
  "anthropic" adapter authenticates with "x-api-key" against a hardcoded
  api.anthropic.com, whereas the fleet agent-vault injects Anthropic as an OAuth
  Bearer, so a dummy x-api-key is rejected (ADR-049 Context; findings/fabro-spike/
  03-fabro-launch.md, 03c-shim-u5-close.md). This scenario pins the launcher
  behavior that closes that last blocker on the REAL launch path: when
  bc-container launches a BC on the fabro orchestrator path, the launcher STARTS
  the baked anthropic-oauth-shim in-container and points fabro's
  "[llm.providers.anthropic] base_url" at it (127.0.0.1:8788), so an in-container
  agent's dummy x-api-key flows shim -> HTTPS_PROXY -> agent-vault -> real OAuth,
  with fabro's native vault still holding only "__PLACEHOLDER__".

  REPRODUCES fabro-orchestration/02 (@scenario_hash:9c7b4e8280665239) VIA THE
  REAL LAUNCH PATH. Scenario 02 pins the credential contract as a LEAD-PROCESS
  behavior (ADR-049): a dummy x-api-key reaches a real OAuth 200 via the shim and
  agent-vault while fabro's secret store holds only placeholders. THIS scenario
  pins the bc-launcher WIRING that makes that contract true on an actual
  "bc-container launch" — the launcher-observable half. It DISTINGUISHES from,
  and does not duplicate: scenario 02 (the round-trip contract itself), scenario
  73 (shim merely PRESENT + launchable), scenario 75 (def present + vault
  placeholder, the static invariant), and bc-launcher 45/46/50 (the bc-container
  Claude/GitHub credential path, not the fabro provider wiring).

  WHAT THE BC BUILDS AND CHECKS STRUCTURALLY. The bc-launcher build host lacks
  agent-vault and a live LLM, so the full dummy-x-api-key -> real-OAuth-200
  round-trip is verified LIVE at the LEAD end-to-end and is deliberately NOT in
  this scenario's in-container checkable core. What the BC builds and verifies
  structurally is the LAUNCHER WIRING that the round-trip rides on, all
  observable without agent-vault:
    - the baked shim (S1, /usr/local/bin/anthropic-oauth-shim) is STARTED
      in-container by the launcher and is listening on 127.0.0.1:8788;
    - fabro's effective settings carry "[llm.providers.anthropic] base_url =
      http://127.0.0.1:8788/v1" (adapter left "anthropic", NO format
      translation — ADR-049 D2; canonical line: findings/fabro-spike/fabro-defs/
      anthropic-oauth-shim/settings.toml.snippet);
    - the def's native fabro vault still holds only "__PLACEHOLDER__" (ADR-049
      D1), and no real credential is written into fabro's native secret store on
      this launch path.
  The behavior it pins is the REAL wiring (the shim the agent actually reaches,
  the base_url fabro actually uses); only its at-the-wire consummation folds into
  the lead end-to-end check.

  UNDER provider=local, fabro nodes inherit the parent container's HTTPS_PROXY +
  SSL_CERT_FILE, so the shim's urllib forwards through agent-vault with no
  per-run env plumbing (ADR-049 D3 follow-up: the in-container target already
  carries HTTPS_PROXY + CA, so the spike's [run.environment.env] workaround falls
  away). The shim stores NO secret — it only normalizes header shape.

  LAUNCH PARITY (ADR-050). This is additional wiring the launcher establishes on
  the fabro orchestrator path; it changes nothing about the launch interface
  itself (tmux default unchanged, shop-msg mailbox preserved). (Targets
  shopsystem-bc-launcher / bc-base, owned per ADR-021.)

  @scenario_hash:8b5a1b9e5499293b
  Scenario: launching a BC on the fabro orchestrator path starts the in-container anthropic-oauth-shim and points fabro's anthropic provider base_url at it while the native fabro vault holds only placeholders
    Given the shopsystem-bc-launcher BC is installed
    And bc-container launch is run for BC name "shopsystem-messaging" on the fabro orchestrator launch path
    And the container "bc-shopsystem-messaging" is running on the pinned bc-base image that carries the baked anthropic-oauth-shim at "/usr/local/bin/anthropic-oauth-shim" (scenario 73, @scenario_hash:a3512aedb8763150) and the self-contained fabro def whose native vault holds only "__PLACEHOLDER__" (scenario 75, @scenario_hash:2dfefe2ba81e418d)
    When the fabro credential wiring the launcher established in that running container is inspected structurally, without requiring a reachable agent-vault or any live LLM call
    Then the baked anthropic-oauth-shim has been started in-container by the launcher and is listening on "127.0.0.1:8788", so an in-container agent's Anthropic traffic has a local endpoint to send its dummy x-api-key to
    And fabro's effective settings carry "[llm.providers.anthropic]" with "base_url" set to "http://127.0.0.1:8788/v1" pointing the built-in anthropic provider at that shim, with the adapter left as "anthropic" so the shim speaks native Anthropic Messages format in both directions and no OpenAI-to-Anthropic format translation is introduced (ADR-049 D2)
    And the def's native fabro vault still holds only the literal value "__PLACEHOLDER__" for every provider-key and token slot it declares, with no real credential written into fabro's native secret store on this launch path (ADR-049 D1)
    And the real Anthropic credential is nowhere in fabro's native vault or the shim's own configuration on this launch path: it rides only the agent-vault surface on the wire via the container HTTPS_PROXY (the dummy x-api-key to in-container shim to HTTPS_PROXY to agent-vault to real OAuth 200 round-trip that fabro-orchestration/02, @scenario_hash:9c7b4e8280665239, pins is exercised live at the lead end-to-end and is not part of this scenario's in-container checkable core)
